Taiwan Stocks: Compal Electronics, Hannstar, Sino-American

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-08-11T01:40:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/compal-electronics-fubon-sino-american-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:28 a.m. in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 178.51 points, or 2.3 percent, to
7,557.81.  Compal Electronics Inc. (2324)  (2324 TT) lost 2.3 percent to
NT$28.20. The world’s second-largest laptop maker may miss its
shipment target of 48 million  notebook computers  this year
because of weak demand in Europe and the U.S., Digitimes
reported today, without saying where it got the information.
Chang Chih-ming, an investor relations official, declined to
comment on the report.  HannStar Display Corp. (6116)  (6116 TT) dropped 3.8 percent to
NT$2.81. The flat panel maker received an investigation report
issued by the Korea Fair Trade Commission alleging it and other
liquid-crystal-display panel manufacturers violated competition
law, according to a company statement to the Taiwan stock
exchange yesterday.  Sino-American Silicon Products Inc. (5483)  (5483 TT) surged 7
percent to NT$69.20, set for the steepest rise since Feb. 14.
The Taiwanese provider of silicon used in solar cells plans to
acquire Covalent Materials Corp.’s wafer business for 35 billion
yen ($456 million) to gain market share in  Japan , Sino-American
said in a faxed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
